1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 27 MRSA §505, sub-§2, ¶D, as amended by PL 2023, c. 9, §1, is further
3 amended by amending subparagraph (2) to read:
4 (2) The historic property that is the subject of the grant application must be listed
5 on the National Register of Historic Places as authorized by the National Historic
6 Preservation Act of 1966 or, have been nominated to the register by the
7 commission or have been designated as a historic property by a municipal historic
8 preservation ordinance.
9 Sec. 2. Eligibility for historic preservation bond proceeds. No later than
10 November 30, 2025, the Maine Historic Preservation Commission shall adopt rules
11 pursuant to the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 27, section 504, subsection 2-A regarding the
12 disbursement of bond proceeds authorized by Public Law 2023, chapter 653 to establish a
13 process for properties in the State that are not on the National Register of Historic Places
14 but have been designated as historic properties by municipal historic preservation
15 ordinances to receive funding through the bond proceeds.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This bill amends the eligibility requirements for grants through the Maine Historic
1188 Preservation Commission for the preservation and restoration of historic properties to allow
1199 eligibility for properties that have been designated as historic properties by municipal
2200 historic preservation ordinances. The bill also directs the Maine Historic Preservation
2211 Commission to adopt rules regarding the disbursement of bond proceeds authorized by
2222 Public Law 2023, chapter 653 to establish a process for properties in the State that are not
2233 on the National Register of Historic Places but have been designated as historic properties
2244 by municipal historic preservation ordinances to receive funding through the bond
2255 proceeds.
